76561197990994295,Recommended,236150,34643822,Posted: 31 August,all,Lhetre,"The game does many things well. Once you try and play as intended, the UI becomes more intuitive and the gameplay fluid. Ignore the plot if you are easily frustrated by weak stories, it does help you visit the map though.Some tips to appreciate the game.- Use mouse and keyboard to play, they work perfectly. This is a casual game, not a flying simulation, you don't need a joystick.- You need to master mouse3. Mouse1 to fly, mouse2 to fire and the ever so important mouse3 for the context menu.Mouse3 is your friend.- Equipment is vital and plentiful, use and abuse it. You may take on bigger enemies than you if you understand how equipement works.- Improve your systems as soon as you can, it is worth the expense.-""Fire at Will"" takes the place of dogfight in this game.You have equipped the best weapons you can, let them do their job. Turrets certainly do not concentrate their fire on one target, but they will do short work on weak enemies and leave the strongest for the end.- Use ""v"" while flying to inspect enemy ships, and see if they are worth attacking or it is better to run away.- Use ""k"" to see your ship and your target at the same time. This is meant to help you capping (but I prefer a different method).- Verifiy enemy difficulty before attacking. Simple as that.- Trade is viable as soon as you can afford a freighter, but you'll earn experience a little bit too fast in my opinion. Some short circuits (buy at station A sell some at station B while buying more, then sell what is left at station C) have been implemented in the game, you don't need to run through half the map to make a living (not like in other games which are developed to complicate your life).- Capping enemies is the best way of making money. Read a guide if you find it difficult.- Capping is limited only by the number of marines sold in stations, when they run out of marines, you have to change station.- Regions have a level of difficulty, if too many enemies attack you, go to a quieter place. On the other hand, friendly regions bordering with enemy regions are perfect hunting grounds.- If you feel overpowered fly towards neutral, or even better, allied space, where other ships will help you.Things I liked.- Combat, once I understood how to cap and the importance of ""Fire at Will"".- The easy way of trade.- T-portal system.- Ship improvements and enhancements.- Ship models.- Game progression.- Side missions scaling.- No bugs.Neutral.- The plot.- Station models.- A little bit too easy after the initial (relative) difficulty spike.- Voice acting. They are not necessarily bad, on the contrary, they tried to give some depth to their parts, but they are not native English speakers, which sometimes is even a postive point.Tthree points where the game could have been improved on.- You know what you are targeting only if you are looking directly at it, no information on your target if it is out of your field of view, aside from its direction.- Once you become allied with half the factions the game becomes too easy.- Capping ships is overpowered, it becomes less and less hazardous the more you invest in improvements on your ship.tl;dr;I was quite pleased beating six ships, of which two were dubbed ""impossible"".Edit: spelling."
76561197960687390,Recommended,236150,28685699,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,Insomniac,"Amusing and pretty game.  I had fun.  Once I got the hang of capturing ships, the difficulty level dropped.  To be fair, I haven't tried tackling any of the veteran bounties, yet.  I understand that those are considerably more difficult since they will actually put up a fight and deploy counter-measures.The reputation system in this game is very simple: you gain +20 reputation for completing tasks for law-abiding factions and -20 reputation for completing missions for pirate factions.  I would expect reputation gain to drop more significantly and gain more slowly as it does in many other space sim games (e.g. Eve, X3, ...).  As it is, if you're low on cash, simply cap a ship and you'll be back in black.Pro:- Pretty- Lots of ships- Large mapCon:- Not a whole lot of variety or depth.- Different ships don't seem different enough (i.e. play style remains largely the same)- Voice acting is terrible; would have been better without.- Overly simplistic reputation system (see above)."
