,Not Recommended,236150,33766181,Posted: 24 July,all,Ser Robyn Highart,"It could be fun. However a very clunky control scheme gets in the way. By that I mean the fact that to simply look around the ship, one has to press two keys to enter a ""turret mode"", then ""targeting"", and then the camera follows a target reticule, instead of a 1:1 mouse control. This is terrible in battles and travel alike.In battles, the information on a hostile ship is tethered to its position in space. Therefore, to see any info like distance, health, danger, one must be looking at it. Without direct line of sight, all one gets is an arrow pointing to where it is. Trying to fly the ship, keep an eye on its vitals, whilst also trying to get a look at the enemy ship that is behind you is bloody tedious. I eneded up just not bothering, and stayed in the most intuative control mode, forcing me to simply circle around until the enemy came into view. This made the battle boring and devoid of tactics.The game is beautiful and the ships look cool. One can even name their ship and have the name appear on the hull. There is also quite a bit of long distance travel to do. Combine those things and what happens? The player ends up wanting to look at the vistas and maybe get a nice cinematic view of the ship on a long and uneventful voyage. However, with this clunky camera it just doesn't happen. Firstly, because it simply sucks in the first place, being slow and restricted, with a million different modes and keys. Secondly, because once the destination is reached, one has to reverse all that crap and get into the proper control mode in order to be able to fight. Constant mode and targetting switching is just tedious and not worth the effort.If they had just copied the controls of the countless 3rd person space games out there, at least the game would be playable. I could see myself playing it quite a bit. But when I can't even comfortably look at the freaking ship up close, from an angle I like whilst exploring then I just cannot reccomend or play it. In short, the ship is a chore to handle. I'm not saying the game is too hard, bwaaaah. I'm saying simple things take too many steps to perform and are badly implemented.When a mod comes out to overhaul the camera, I will come back and recommend the game."
