76561198067328400,Recommended,236150,10021712,"Posted: 4 May, 2014",all,taiter,"This is one of those games that just looks so damn good, you can't help but just stop and look around at where you are sometimes. Add in it's intuitive UI and control setup, epic combat mechanics, and ease of navigation and you have the makings of what could be one of the best games in the genre.Even in it's beta form, there is enough sandbox, 4x, space sim fun to make it worth the price of admission. With the new modes and 'scenarios' promised for the full version (hopefully one of which is a story campaign that's epic enough to keep up with the setting and gameplay), this one could turn in to a true gem (No pun. Shut up. Don't judge me).That said there are a few balancing issues with the missions at the moment. Right now, the randomly generated missions seem to cap their pay at around 5000-10000 credits a piece, and none of them give you more than 100 XP, no matter how far you level up. The only way get enough XP to meet the prequisite for buying a better ship is to kill bad guys. LOTS of them.This makes buying a frieghter and becoming a miner or a trader pointless. Not that you would ever be able to afford that new ship since the pricetag for anything better than the frigate you start with starts at around 3,000,000. Factor in expenses and costly ship upgrades you have to keep up with and after 10 hours of play, I only had about a third of that. 30+ hours of play before you can even buy your first ship seems like a bit much to me. The missions are way too repetitive to justify that much grind.Same story with trading and mining. Mining never makes you more than a couple thousand creds a trip, and the amount of XP you get is effectively useless. It's even worse with trading. I haven't noticed any difference in prices of goods from one place to another, which means you can't make money (or XP for that matter) buying low at one place and selling high at another like you can in games like X3.Add a story mode, balance the missions so the pay and XP increase steadily as your level goes up, make them a bit less repetitive, and make the trading/mining mechanics of the game more lucrative, and this game would be just a tick below perfect."
