,Recommended,236150,32014000,Posted: 28 May,all,weatherseed,"Space, the final frontier. These are the voyages of a game that has been a lot of fun.There are similar games out there to this, no doubt. In fact, it seems to be one of the great truths in life that, no matter where in time you are so long as it's after the release of Elite, very little will change besides the graphics. What does matter are the controls, exploration, the story, and (let's face it) combat.The controls are, simply put, very basic. This is good for cruising in your Space Ferrari through the galaxy. There are no headaches to be found here.Exploration? Save for a few interesting space anomalies you have to learn to navigate and finding new stations to trade with... Well... You won't find much here to work with. The galaxy itself is very 2D, which is helpful for navigation, but you rarely decide to veer wildly off the beaten path unless those pirates REALLY♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥you off.Story and plot in this game are, while interesting, fairly light. You can play with or without it. Having done both, I'm actually a fan of sticking to the plot. There's still a lot to do and see in the galaxy, but you'd likely never think of going to these places without a little hand holding.Last, and by no means least, is combat. I'll say it plain. This was a lot of fun for me. The smaller ships force you to line up your shots and take the time to learn more about the combat system. Larger ships get, my favorite, turrets. You can either fly about, positioning yourself to take less damage and letting your turrets automatically target enemies or take control yourself to aim at that dreadnought that just decided to pop in for a fight.My one sole complaint concerning combat are the missiles. I hate them. Powerful, yes, but fickle.Each ship, of which there are many, can be customized very nicely. What made things even more fun were the mods. I had a great deal of fun flying around in the Galaxy-class starship from Star Trek.I will note that this game does not have the intricate controls and fleet building that the X series has. It doesn't have the exploration that Elite: Dangerous or NMS have either. What it does is find a happy place in the middle and let you kick some space butt."
