76561198009287858,Recommended,236150,11777227,"Posted: 19 August, 2014",all,CommanderEcks,"I have constantly shunned the games that say ""We are currently building our Beta version... blah blah blah."" As these game companies often move into the vapor ware that we all so hate.  Knowing that; and knowing that I have been seeking a great 4x game, (I just KNEW that one was out there somewhere), I purchased this game in the Beta 0.8 state.Now one might expect a lot of bugs and CTD from a large scale game like this.  With the small additions coming evey couple weeks I would expect the same.That all being said: 8/10 in its current form.I find this game amazing for a number of reasons.  The 4x aspect of this game is in place and you are allowed to pick ""free fly"" mode and just enjoy.  Fully armed pirates will come try to kill you, and you have to defend ships that ask for help if you are in the region.The speed of some space sim games have put me off, you know, the three minutes slowly flying to the jump gate or what not.  Well SG2 gives you the ability to max out your engines with the push of one button and cruise wherever you want QUICKLY.The speed of gaining levels is really great, you feel like you are doing something after you start killing pirates.  Getting an immediate advantage, then leveraging that advantage to kill more raiders and bandits.  You level up quickly because the max level seems to be above 70.  With several hours in I have reached level 15 and have an amazing 2.8M credit ship.  So you can play for a short period and feel great about the results.  But please note, this easy mode still allows for the chance that bandits get fed up and come to kill you.  I have been ambushed 3x and killed them only once... died in a burst of flame the other two times.  Love it, cannot wait for the story line."
