76561197998573742,Recommended,236150,11346430,"Posted: 21 July, 2014",all,Nephtys,"Do you remember the space sim Elite, or perhaps Freelancer, or the X universe games?If like me you have been looking for a new game to scratch that space sim itch, then look no further than Starpoint Gemini 2.Though still in Beta, this is already a very polished game with most of the content needed to get a good feel for the finished product in place.The game allows you to roam freely and explore, with multiple factions and dynamic missions, ( a campaign mode will be added for release ) there is already plenty to keep you occupied for many an hour.The game also has a great community following, with regular contact from the dev team at LGM who are very willing to engage with the players and to listen to their input.If like me you have been disappointed by the recent offerings in the space sim genre, then get yourself a copy of this game."
76561198089492079,Recommended,236150,11682701,"Posted: 12 August, 2014",all,SpecterCody,"**UPDATE**(9/30/14)The game is now at full release. I will break the game into categories below and comment my opinion on them.(+ means positive, * means neutral, - means negative)Gameplay:+Fast, exciting and action packed combat+Plenty of ship customization+Controls are fairly intuitive and easy to use+Plenty to explore and collect+Moddability*RPG style progression (skilltree and leveling)*Unrealistic physics makes things easier to play but undesirable to some*No multiplayer-Limited to 3 class choice on start of new game, cannot change later-Unrealistic scale of universe (mainly planets and stars are WAY too small)-No docking animation for stations-Occasional crashesStory:*Typical story, nothing special-Bad voice acting/racial steriotypes detract from story-Some missions ""vanish"" from map meaning you must load old save to continue storyGraphics/Sound:+Good quality graphics and visuals+Good sound effects and music overall-FPS takes a large hit during a few mission scenes or large battles-Aforementioned poor voice acting-Visual bugs with space background images (visible ""skyboxes"") are occasionally seenOverall Impression:This game has been quite a fun experience coming from a fan of RPG style games. The level progression system and skilltree coupled with a highly moddable ship means you have a reason to keep playing and improving. You are able to pilot anything from a tiny gunship to a powerful carrier but do not expect to be a fleet commander. Emphasis on is your ship. The story gives you a reason to play but it is not where the game shines. The most fun to be had is exploring, lucrative bounties and close encounters with tough enemies. Its a shame the game crashes on occassion and the story has some bugs. These things will hopefully be ironed out soon."
