76561198028609919,Recommended,236150,11327675,"Posted: 19 July, 2014",all,schrodingerwang,"Great Potential.I have not touched the first Gemini, this is my first time into Gemini world. But I have been a huge fan for Freelancer, X3 series and EVE. Right now it feels like this game is pretty close to Freelancer in the sense of combat and universe design. It provides a huge universe for you to explore, combat whatever or whoever you see as enemy and different ways to gather credit.So far I think there are several problems with this game.1. The universe feels detached from the player. Of course this has something to do with the absense of campaign and a main plot, but the universe still feels lonely, even worse than X3.2. Some of the UIs need more work. Sometimes it is difficult to find out more information about an item. I hope the game can impliment something like the info page in EVE, which gives a full list of all the details about an item and you do not have to go around the place to find out or get confused.3. The combat. The combat is very similar to X3, you have several batteries on diffent side of your ship and they can be controlled independent of the ship. This is OK but when you are engaged in a multi ship combat, you will most likely lose the sense of situation. I hope a third person view can be implimented. Also the weapon/damage/energy balance feels a little strange. Most weapon will suck your energy dry while taking less than 25% of your enemy's shield. It looks like it is encouraging hit and run tactics which is perfectly fine for small agile ships. What bothers me is the big boys like battleships do not get a substantial upgrade on the battery energy.Other than those, I think this is an exciting game and it has a lot of potential.PS, it looks like the game has some hints of a fleet feature. I hope they can do it right because fleet in X3 is a nightmare. Eithre do it right, or don't do it at all."
