76561198000573369,Recommended,236150,11316412,"Posted: 19 July, 2014",all,Vlakvarkie,"Starpoint Gemini 2 – ReviewHi everyone,This is my first ever review that I am writing.  I just bought the game last night and started playing this morning.  Before buying I read some other reviews just to get an idea if I should take the leap into the void.  Well, I took the leap (based on some good reports) and what I found was far from a void.Here are some bulleted remarks:•	I was immediately impressed by the structure and layout of the game as soon as I entered. No nonsense.  Get in and get on with it.  I loved that.•	There is a lot of depth to the game with a creative insight to usability.•	Personally I like the way the tutorial is incorporated into the start and the way that it is presented (simplicity and effectiveness).  Here are some thoughts:o	The font on the display was a little difficult for me to read (15`` screen, max settings), but that could be due to the screen size, not sure).o	At the start where you select from the three types of careers, it also might need a better font and colour scheme (just my personal opinion) to read a bit better. Everything still very good, don’t get me wrong.o	Would also advise to have a smart lady voice to read out tutorials as you go along, whilst displaying text (always keep the text).  Do not overcook and cause annoyance.o	Just mention within the tutorial that a “Collect all” indicator will pop up (after you destroyed an asteroid) once your close to the collectable. Was a bit unsure at first how I would collect, but became obvious when the pop up appeared to collect when I destroyed an asteroid up close.•	In- game graphics, display hub and layout is amazing. Great job.•	I absolutely love the small tutorial button, accessible at any time, especially when getting use to the game (keep it).•	Like that I can scroll up and down with mouse wheel in tutorial and other hud displays.•	Like that there is a info bubble over icons and other aspects.•	Love the idea of boarding and capturing ships and that you can do different things with those ships, brilliant.•	Great idea to be able to launch the whole or individually selected fighter wings and that there is criteria added to the fighter wings as well.•	Personally I like that there are asteroids all around to get some loot from and that it’s not just in pockets.I am a teacher by occupation and therefore I like clear and structured instructions.  I think the developers got this done well and that the ""polishing"" is going to make the tutorials and overall game experience even better and better.I love this game already and I have only been playing for a couple of hours.  I am super excited about what it is yet to deliver and the hours and hopefully years of joy I will get from venturing through this vast space full of life and challenges.If you love space sims you will not regret buying this game.  It is definitely worth the money for me below $17.I will try and write more reviews on the game as I continue to play.  Man, this is a lot of fun."
