76561198132095561,Recommended,236150,20356814,"Posted: 6 January, 2016",all,Drifter,"Starpoint Gemini 2 is extensive and packs in an incredible amount and variety of content, especially with the two current DLCs. The map itself is evident to this. I myself enjoy the  freeplay mode, as it allows for more customization of my character and allows for a more unique exploration of the world.Not to mention the unique dynamics the game allows, including the combat mechanics, political affiliations, etc.The main achievement of this game- its size- is also part of an issue that it has. This issue is the immersion level.Apart from the storylines and cutscenes, the only way to interact with other ships is to either repair them or (more often) fight them. Such a big world with only limited interaction can begin to feel... empty.In a universe potrayed by Starpoint Gemini, such an expansive space, the aspect of trade would be very important.I suggest a new dynamic with other ships that would allow the player to trade with them. In essence, using the same model as that when docked in a space station but with friendly freighters, carriers, etc.Another suggestion is to add randomized large scale battles between rivaling territories. It seems odd to me that a system in such turmoil has so little actual conflict after the storyline. Not to mention being part of large scale battles is a thrilling experience.Finally (I am unsure if your system allows for this), a very nice addition would be visible upgrades or customizations to the player's ship. For instance, one could buy a new engine/thruster for a ship and visibly replace the one their ship has or armor upgrades that visibly cover the ship's hull.These additions would add some much needed immersion and keep the gameplay fresh without the need for another DLC."
