76561197973119003,Not Recommended,236150,12287893,"Posted: 29 September, 2014",all,Riptor,"I can only recommend this game for people who have no problem with simply flying around blowing things up and nothing else. Because that is essentially everything you will do in this game. Blow things up.Blow enemy ships up, blow wreckages up, blow asteroids up...The trading system is a bare bones basic ""pick things up that enemies drop and sell them at the nearest station""Sometimes you might come across illegal goods that might have the local authorities in a hissy fit but thats about it. Theres no system in place to actually figure out the best place to sell your goods so trade routes are a chore and not really worth it.The graphics are really nice but poorly optimized and some of the graphics options are locked at ""high"" like ship details and cant be lowered.The balancing is also all over the place with alot of weaponsystems being rather useless (all beam weapons for example) compared to the railgun type wich obliterates everything. Also even thought you can hire mercenaries to fly with you for a ingame monthly fee it never feels like you are actually in command of a fleet... wich is another missed oportunity.All in all what this game lacks is content... alot of content and a healthy dose of polish. There is a really great game hiding in starpoint gemini 2 but it just doesnt has any meat on its bones.So at its current state i can only recommend this game to hardcore space sim lovers who are starved for a title where you controll a battleship instead of a flimsy little one man fightercraft.  If you feel like youre that type you will get a lot of optical diverse ship designs...Thought there is hope that the modding community will jump in and polish things up a bit."
