76561198268193917,Recommended,236150,31319280,Posted: 23 April,all,Laceon,"Star Point Genimini 2 is an open world space sim with tons of ships to choose from and plenty of space to blow them up in. The combat is fairly basic but in a good fight can become tactical in some manners, such as shield/armor/speed tanking. The weapons are not too exciting, small variety and needs some randomization to help with the very few good weapons in the game (Rail guns are basically the best i have noted, accuracy and dmg).The graphics are pretty and the ships are fun to look at.  Though even on low settings my computer has a lot of lag when traveling from sector to sector (specs below*).  It runs alright on a laptop but still laggy.The map is fairly big with random events that are basically all you do, which in turn makes the story line very bland.  The story line itself is lethargic and not very engaging and the voice acting does not help.  The missions get fairly repetitve, go here blow this up or repair that thing, however, there is a fair variety of ways to make cash.  I thought its cool you can capture enemy ships and sell them. Trading and mining are pretty mediocre, but in a big ship you can haul more. You need a constant income to keep up your fleet, this can be challenging sometimes because you just bought a bunch of shiny stuff, which will just bottom out later in the game because you have the best crap.All in all i recommend this game, its pretty dope and simple to play, it definately needs some balancing and factions dont really matter.  It can be a little CPU heavy at times on a laptop.  Be prepared for a lot of down times, there can be a lot of flying around to do.7.5/10Pros:Fun and Easy GameplayGood Looking Ships And Tons Of ThemChallengingAddictiveGood Diversity Of Money MakingCons:Lame Story LineHUD Needs Some Help (Mostly Needs A Target Disply On The HUD)Controls Can Be A Little WonkyNeeds Balancing (Ships and Weapons / Not Enough Actual Variety)Faction Relations 