76561198019182548,Not Recommended,236150,12511143,"Posted: 16 October, 2014",all,Bob The Goat,"Frankly the worst game I've played in a LONG time.The flight controls want to be simple, but they completely destroy physics to make it possible.  When you throttle down from full speed, you stop on a dime, and when you turn the front of your ship, all of your momentum magically matches the new direction you're pointing.  The old game ""Darkstar One"" has a similar ""fly-by-mouse"" control scheme, but has at least SOME concept of physics.Combat in this one is pointless: 50% of the time, the enemies are blown up by mysteriously appearing ""friends"" before you can even fire a shot, 40% of the time they can be killed with ""stop next to them and blow them up with your laser/railgun/whatever"" tactics, and 10% of the time you get jumped by a ship so much more powerful than you that it cannot be killed or run away from.If you get tired of the pointless combat, there's a pointless trade economy (any station seems to buy anything you happen to be carrying, so all you do to ensure massive profit is buy anything that's green on the merchant's side, and sell anything that's green on your side).Most of all, there's the insanely boring flying between points...  Space is pretty big, and there's only a minimal form of go-fast mode (not time accelleration, but ""Power to Engines""), but that only speeds things up by maybe 2-5x, so that most of the time between pointless combat and pointless trading is spent in boring autopilot, flying between waypoints and watching fake looking asteroids and plasma outside your windscreen.  And if you happen to run into an actual asteroid... no big deal, you bounce off.  Literally 2-7 minutes of uneventful flight between each encounter.As a side note, the campaign voice acting (including the player) is some of the worst I've heard in years.  Accents change randomly mid-sentence, and the pacing and stresses are often strange."
