76561198030653400,Not Recommended,236150,12453413,"Posted: 11 October, 2014",all,doug.white,"This is a game like X3 where you fly around in space and can take on a lot of roles, trader, pirate, etc.  The game is pretty and the space scenes are very nice.  The graphics are smooth and pretty interesting.  The game itself is pretty boring.  I usually play as a trader/adventurer in X3.  So, the ships are all pretty boring and the number systems you can use in them is not very interesting either.  Basically, there are different types of weapons you can mount but they are all pretty much the same.  The game tries to make them interesting by using mods and personal skills but it's too complex (there is very little documentation) and too simple (basically every mod is just a slight variation in the effect of the weapon).  The ships are the same way, they get bigger and badder, but the bad guys scale right up too so you basically just fly around and each mission is about the same.  There are a very limited number of missions in the game and you either tranport cargo, a vip, assassinate a bad guy, or repair a station.  All are very very easy to complete even when you choose ones marked hard.  Every now and then someone just flat takes you out but there is no middle ground.  After about 20 hours, it's just the same thing over and over again.  Trade is very simplistic and since it doesn't really cost you anything to fly around, you just buy low and sell high.  The worst part is the cost.  Ships and weapons cost a fortune but missions and trade generates very little per outing so it takes thousands of missions to generate a new ship.  Resale values are ridiculously low (for instance a ship that costs 10 million credits has a sale value of about 2M).  The only way to really make money is to cap ships.  That works.  The bad news is, that is hard to do effectively since there is little to no control over your other units in combat and they just shoot up everything.  The flight controls are awful.  Using the keyboard you have all these other combat mods that are hard to use and limited.  Mostly, there is no documention of anything so you don't really know what to do.  The tutorial is just some tidbits that get so annoying you turn it off.  Bottom line, this game is boring and has no depth.  Maybe mods will add to it in the future, but for now I got over it pretty fast."
