76561197970480316,Not Recommended,236150,12449995,"Posted: 11 October, 2014",all,Leviathan,"After a long consideration, whether I should give a thumb up or down, I have to go with the negative.  It's really borderline if you ask me...if they'd ask me to give a percentage, I would give 50%While the visuals are nice and the option of upgrading the ship with various devices and ""powers"" and so is the roleplaying element of giving stats, there is something empty about this game.You fly around in a 3rd person /behind/ view of a ship and you navigate through space by an interactive 2D starmap.  You do missions, which are mainly destroy other ships or follow the main campaign , which is pretty much flying to various location and ...drumroll...destroy other ships.The way it's done is by trying to position your ship so your main guns get the best angle and this requires moving your camera view while keeping an eye on your speed and direction.   Also don't forget to activate your ""powers"", which are usually about your shields, your guns or extra chance to hit ...similar abilities you'd find in many fantasy rpgs.While this may be fun for many...and the argument of ""but so are other similar games have a similar gameplay"" , this game doesn't really push any boundaries.   You could easily see it as a copycat of Starflight from the late 80s, but that had more features (planetary landing and exploration).The game just feels shallow, despite the best attempts and best intentions of the developers and there is a huge thumb up for their efforts and communication with the public while making this game, but I'm here to write a review on the game, not the intentions and public relations."
