76561198026545377,Not Recommended,236150,12360583,"Posted: 4 October, 2014",all,Kejal,"In its current form (version 1.0003) I can not recommend the game. Though it is by no means awful, there is simply not enough content to stay interested longer than a day or two.Weak points:1. Static universe: Dockable stations and space objects like satellites/gas collectors are all fixed and indestructible. Ships simply spawn, get destroyed and spawn again. Player actions do not have any impact on the universe whatsoever which is a shame because all territories (hexes on the starchart) have an owner and player let wars which lead to territories being conquered would make the universe much more dynamic.2. Factions are uninspired and interchangeable (see 3.). There is no dynamic between for example traders and pirates. Either a faction is good or evil and will attack all other evil or good factions. All factions could be reduced to 3, one good, one evil and one ""I hate you no matter what you do"" faction.3. Weak reputation system: Your reputation with a faction is based solely on your alignment (good/evil). All factions are either aligned with good or evil (there are no neutral factions). When having a high(good) reputation all good factions will be friendly and you can not antagonize a single one of them without antagonizing all4. User Interface: The game lacks shortcuts for basic actions like docking. There is only a ""quick action"" shortcut which is used for dropping fast travel AND docking. Should you be in range for docking you will dock otherwise drop fast travel and slowly crawl towards the station until you can dock.5. Missions: The current mission types are extremely basic kill, protect, fly to and transport missions. They get reptetitive fast.6. Voice acting is bad: Even if you try to get immersed in the campaign storyline, chances are good that the awful voice acting will make it impossible.Strong points:1. Seamless universe2. Fast travel systems are interesting and remain useful throughout the game with unique pros and consI recommend to wait a few month for either the devs or modding community to add more content to the game."
