,Not Recommended,236150,13683718,"Posted: 29 December, 2014",all,baby jesus,"This game has a lot of heart and good intentions, but has a lot of implementation issues as of version 1.2.It seems to be under active development, but the issues I have with it run so deep that it is unlikely they will get fixed. Everything that is not world sim is implemented as cheaply as possible, and to fix all of these issues would never make business sense.- Tutorals are non-interactive and your first 5-10 minutes of your experience is you being interrupted by annoying dialog boxes with way too many bullet points to read in one go.- The planets and bases do not feel like places, and are just a UI screen with some static concept art as a wallpaper if you are lucky. There is no docking animation. Space stations don't even rate background art. Hence there is no feeling of exploration.- The campaign is done entirely via comm chatter and dialog boxes and is incredibly limited. You are not going to meet a character at a bar on a space station. That would need character art, space station art, and space bars for that, which is so far beyond the budget of this game as it is now that it's just never going to happen.- The UI is not finished yet. I stopped playing because I accidentally removed all of my turrets trying to figure out the interface. The button to put them back on didn't work. The only way to figure out what is going on is to do forum searches, but my game was still corrupted because of UI designs so bad it basically looks like the game is broken. If you are 13 you might have the patience for that, I do not.- Considering how tiny the budget is, it is way over-priced. This should be $20 tops.- There are missing sound effects for things (e.g. nothing for tractor beams, picking up scrap, and beam weapon sounds are buggy and have start/stop issues).+ The core sandbox 3d gameplay and navigation, where they did spend their time, is a gem. I hope they can at least make the game playable so I can try and become a pirate fleet commander one day, albeit not in the game I wish it was.Even though I am giving it a thumbs down, it's not a very strong thumbs down. I do plan on revisiting the game in 6 months or so to see how it is. Taken on its own terms, with UI and tutorial improvements the game could be quite enjoyable, even if it's more of a limited and unimmersive sort."
