,Not Recommended,236150,13781511,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,Ass Gorehead,"At first glance this game seemed to have everything I wanted from a RPG/space sim combo, but what started out as an enjoyable experience quickly turned into an exercise in frustration. The game seems to suffer from major balance issues and design flaws.The class system doesn't really contribute much to the gameplay as the only difference between the three classes are 4 skills which hardly seem to affect gameplay other than an animation on activating a skill.Regarding balance, I've played all three classes in campaign and freeroam mode and once you reach around level 12 the game seems to go out of sync with what your character is able to do. All combat missions have enemies rated as 'Impossible' to defeat and unless there happens to be friendlies in the area you're pretty much doomed. It also seems impossible to stay alive longer than a few seconds in hostile space as you'll be swarmed by enemies against which you stand no chance. So the sandbox is in reality confined to space in the vicinity of friendly stations.Combat is clunky as most of the time you'll be battling the camera view instead of the enemies who will be off-screen for the majority of the fight. This means that manual combat isn't an option.Making money to buy better ships is also a bit of a chore as it takes forever to make the roughly 2 million credits you'll need to buy your first decent ship. What seems to be the fastest way to make some money is by boarding and selling enemy ships which is also made almost impossible by friendly NPCs tending to blow up the ship you're trying to capture with all your troops on board.All in all I'm rather disappointed to be so let down by this game as on the surface it really has the potential to be excellent."
