76561198040276656,Not Recommended,236150,14176062,"Posted: 26 January, 2015",all,teMELEEn,"SHORT: If you want to paly space arcade which is quite easy and has kinda little for you to do (you like to do same thing over and over), then this game is for you. If you want to play space sim that is more difficult and real, play evochron mercenary or some X series (Id prefer evochron, X in my view is much shallower than most of the people would tell).*********************************************LONG: ok i waited for some sale for this game for quite some time now as I am a huge space games fan. So when the price went down I went ahead and bought it. Its not a bad game, it just feels... unfinished. My points below:QUEST LINE - is kinda ok. I got lost time to time in who is who, but its not hard to follow if you pay attention. Not super enganging tough. If you think about cutscenes, forget it. Youl get just some mediocre voice acting and thats it.SIDE MISSIONS - they are insanely repetitive. There are even no variations on given mission type what so ever. Example - all science misions are about go somwhere, scan something in like 10 seconds and thats it. It does not matter if the diff level is 1 or 40, its always the same (and you can of course do level 40 mission at level 1)... that applies to all non combat missions. Why? I have no idea. Its important to mention that there are like 5 or 6 mission types. And if you think that would not bother you think again, I tought the same... it will.COMBAT: is the only fun thing and even then its really easy to master. If you are careful, you cannot die in this game. If you do, you just did not get the mechanics right cause once you do, you cannot die. Or you got cocky. You either obliterate anything or run away, which is super easy. Just get some higher level railguns and kill everything. But its fun, really... first game I had a feeling of controlling a big ship all by myself.On the other hand theres not really extensive tactics to apply. You can either fire manually (which is impossible as theres no targeting computer... and try to hit 1px big thing floating in space) or auto fire without possibility of selecting a priority target.ECONOMICS: well this is where the whole game sort of breaks down. Theres only one meaningful way to make money - boarding ships and selling them. Really, theres no point in doing anything else for money making, its just not worth the invested time. Doing missions? Hell no, you will get 10x more money from single low level boarded vessel than from any low level mission (and it takes like 1/10 time). Trading or mining? Nah, too much time spent. Hunting for bounties? Even more time spent.One example for all - at level 1 you are able to board basic gunships. Each sell for 30-120K depenging on its liadout. Side mission on the first levels give you around 10k. So why the hell would you wanna do them except when you need to level up?At the end of the day you will do just these things in this game:1. hang around enemy territory near friendly station and board anything you can board (its not hard, just basic math + some upgrades). After you save enough money, go leveling.2. do side missions just for XP (power leveling, not fun at all) to get to next rank3. byu new ship, repeat step 14. at any given time do the main quest (because why not)You could do more, but the thing is - why would you? And dont go all out on me with role playing... thats human nature - doing the most effective things to achieve a goal. I dont see why should I go mining if I can make much more money much more easily with much less time spent.ARMAMENTis unbalanced. Actually theres no level requirement for any equipment/upgrades/weapons, just for ships. So its very easy to go OP, cause you never have money problem (boarding) so you can buy the best stuff there is straight on. Of course you dont put max level weapons on the basic gunship because of energy consumption, but you get the idea.Also theres not much to upgrade. I got to the point where at level 35 (out of 60!) I had the best ship (frankly why are we allowed to have the best ship at half of level cap?), everything maxed out (best weapons, most expensive upgrades). At that point you can do only one thing that can influnece your ship and that is blueprint hunting. And that is random. totally random. You just have to do all the stuff over and over and over again and wait for a drop (which is not that often). Not fun at all. And you dont need it, you can be OP even without blueprint equip.Also its all transferrable to your new ship so once you upgraded let's say engine to the max, you never change it... even if you do this at level 5, you will stay with that upgrade until level 60.Last thing - only three weapon types + rockets (which are useless) :(ABILITIESThey work fine, but they are not super essential. You can win most of the fights without using any active abilites. Passive abilities are helpful.But its nothing extensive, you basically have 4 active abilities that you upgrade (each with sever sub categories but you usually stick to one or two of them). You get a point each level or so. Passive abilities you can upgrade only once per rank, they have quite nice bonuses to make you even more OP (OP square?).CONCLUSIONThis game feels like bugless beta. There is whole level of depth missing and it feels like the devs just put some stuff together not really thinking about how its gonna work together. The boarding mechanics I find the most troubling as it influences all other aspects of the game, its uper easy and makes you do nothing more than that.It would take some changes to make this game great:- balancing the money incomes to support role playing (again why the hell would I be a miner?)- break down the upgrades to more levels and introduce level requirement for better equip- make different pieces of shields, energy source, engines etc so theres more variety. Right now you only upgrade, but dont replace anything.- make the side missions more interesting and incorporated into the mechanics (e.g. scanning higher level anomalies would need you to go to enemy territory/needs special equipment/whatever + you would need this to unlock upgrades for some of your equipment)- more complex tacticsI really tried to like this game as my record shows, but after this time I just totally lost interest in playing. Maybe I did not figure out some of the stuff I did criticise so in that case let me know. But from my perspective you should not buy this game for full price, $10 tops. It gets old very fast.Id recommend all space freaks to go and crack into evochron mercenary. Its just awesome and after you get through steep learning curve (which is a good sign of complexity) it will reward you with best space feeling I ever had. One more thing to add about evochron - INERTIAL FLYING!!!"
