,Not Recommended,236150,22197064,"Posted: 2 April, 2016",all,Depends On Depends,Boring.
76561198004306894,Not Recommended,236150,22406048,"Posted: 13 April, 2016",all,Strong Sad,"This is a great game that has been damaged beyond use by its creators.  It has a number of mechanics that are quite fun.  There are multiple different ways to move around the universe (including surfing a wormhole) which is fun.  Ship design has enough detail to be fun.  Combat is a mix of skill (manual aiming) and equipment which is also quite fun.  The most fun you can have is capturing another ship.  This requires some amount of skill because the ship has to be damaged a lot in order for your troops to be able to overwhelm the other ship's crew and automated defenses.  All this should make for a very enjoyable game.  However, someone seems to have confused annoyance with difficulty.  When they created higher difficulty levels (normal is quite easy and, therefore, not very fun) they decided to make ship capturing more annoying.  Not harder (by making enemies stronger).  Not riskier (by increasing the chance you will get jumped by pirates looking for two ships for the price of one).  Not more expensive (by increasing the cost of troops).  Not less lucrative (by making the salvage value less or increasing taxes).  They just made it more annoying.  On any level above normal they make is so that other ships in the area continue to fire on the ship you are trying to capture.  This means that unless you are really fast, the friendlies will destroy your prize.  You cannot fight them off because they have overwhelming power and numbers.  This mindless agression is also focused on ships that you have been paid to capture.  Thats right, organizations will put a reward out for the capture of a ship so they can extract vital information, but at the same time, they let their own ships just blow the information up.  Because that makes sense.  The justification for this behavior is that ship capturing is the easiest way to make money so they wanted to make it harder.  But they just made it more annoying by having the AI troll the player.  As a strange consequence of their logic, the higher level difficulties are actually much easier.  Neutral ships will always attack ""bad"" ships as aggressively as possible.  This includes ships that you have been hired to kill.  So you can actually take almost any mission that is a kill mission because the neutrals will kill the enemy for you.  This is much faster than trying to capture ships and towing them back to a station.  You just wander in, let the computer do the mission for you, collect the prize money and wander away again.  Easy, but not very fun.  The creators have been defending their choices for years (there are steam forum posts from at least 2014) so don't expect it to change.  The game might be worth playing if someone has a mod for AI behavior and adjusts the difficulty in a more rational manner.  I'm not quite ready to give up on the game but I definitely cannot recommend playing it as the creators have built it.  Unless you like being trolled by your own computer.  In that case, have fun."
,Not Recommended,236150,13220651,"Posted: 3 December, 2014",all,HefBot 2.0,"A steaming turd of a game and no mistake.The tutorial consists of a couple of pictures and sparse writing which, often, does not even relate to what you are currently even doing in the game.The campaign is dull and the voice acting so wooden I felt like I was watching an Australian soap-opera. I didn't manage to get very far through it before giving up on it for being so grating.The controls are unresponsive and don't even slightly work with a joystick.The game world feels empty and static.There's zero direction like one of the X games, without the sense of actually achieving anything.Then, to add insult to injury, the difficulty curve of the game is based on your pilot level. This is one of the cardinal sins of lazy game development, to make the game adjust its difficulty purely based on how much the player has played it. There are no difficult regions of space, it's all just one homogenous blend where you are far better off just chasing the dollars than the xp bar.Also you can't save whenever you please. Because reasons.Then there's the bugs. Does not support Joysticks. Does not support multiple monitor setups. Weird♥♥♥♥♥♥just happens for no reason with this game.I don't know why I even laid down one cent for this horrid game.Do NOT buy."
