76561198139864451,Not Recommended,236150,17418326,"Posted: 6 August, 2015",all,Ambermonk,"There are 4 things that I don't like about this game...1.  After downloading the game, I discovered that the tactical display key would not function.  I had to do some extensisve remapping to finally get it to work properly.  Until this key was repaired, I lost every single combat that I was in.2.  This game boasts of lots of locations that you can fly to.  This is somewhat true (to a limited extent) and I was quite pleased with all the different kind of space stations.  That said, this game has a huge & glariing problem.  After you dock at a space station, all you get is a rather sterile screen display (like a spreadsheet) THAT IS THE SAME FOR EVERY STARBASE IN THE GAME.  There are no people to meet, no places to see, no contacts to be made, simply nothing!  Other companies have solved this problem with procedural generation, but the Devs didn't seem to be up to it.  Since their game is primarily hard-coded, they will never be able to add the flexibility & expandability that a game like this would do best with.  Every time you go to a starbase, it's the same thing over & over.  This severly limits the playability of the game.3.  Computer shooting games are quite popular these days.  This game takes it a step farther!  This game explicitly advocates cold-blooded murder.  About 85% of all the missions you can undertake are 'assasination' missions.  You are hired to go out and cold-bloodedly kill someone who doesn't even know you.  Oh, you can be a trader if you want, but you won't get very far.  The ship you start out with has a very small cargo hold - far too small to make much money as a trader.  Exacerbating this is the fact that larger ships are prohibitivly expensive.  The only way you can make enough money reasonably fast is to murder people.  If you aren't willing to commit large-scale murder, this game is not going to be for you.  furthurmore, because of all the murder required to play this game, I consider it to be unacceptable for children - and probably for many teenagers as well.  I personally find this relaxed attitude towards murder morally objectionable.4.  I am  also not recommending' this game not because of the game itself, but rather the developer's website.  I registered for the forums on their site and waited for the 'confirmation email.'  It never came.  I tried dozens of times, for days, for the confirmation email to be resent, but to no avail.  I contacted the webmaster to request help, but received no reply.  I submitted a 2nd request for help, but that also was ignored.  Apparently the company cannot be bothered to maintain their own website.  But who knows, I could be just misinformed.  Perhaps the entire company is on vacation, or perhaps the company is no longer in business, or no longer supporting this game.Their pronounced lack of support does not bode well for the future of the game.  Let the buyer beware."
,Not Recommended,236150,11372930,"Posted: 23 July, 2014",all,Reinier,"Pros-------- Beautiful graphics- Unique ship designs and many ships available- The game has a very good shield design that doesnt link all the shields together instead it seperates shields by left, right, front, and back so if your shields go down on the left side of your ship you can shift your ship so that the enemy attacks other parts that still have a shield up.- The game world is pretty huge and reminds me alot of the Star Trek films because you run into nebulas, asteroids, chunks of ice, wormholes, anomalies, and all kinds of cool space stuff that make the game fun to explore.- There is a bounty system so if you want to be a space bounty hunter you can seek out wanted criminals for huge bounty rewards but right now taking enemy ships doesnt work too well.- The price is pretty reasonable, most new games coming out now ask $60 for new releases but this game cost less than half of that.Cons-------- Ship customization leaves a little bit to be desired at the momment because you can pick the ships name, color, and decal but there arent that many decals available, you cant create your own ships with parts you scavanage from destroyed ships, and there are no hood ornaments or other unique additions to add to your ship to really make it feel like your own.- You cant view the inside of  your ship, the decks, the crew, or decorate the interior of your ship.- The current missions in the game are all generic ""deliver item from X location to Y location"" or ""Patrol these waypoints"" which are cut and paste from all the other games, nothing really ground breaking.- Right now in the Early Access you can destroy enemy ships but if they leave a derelict which is like the shell of the ship upon destroying the ship you cant salvage it only destroy it and get the loot that it drops.- Boarding enemy ships is just a numbers game right now, its about who has the most commandos but there is no gear or weapons that you can add to boarding parties to increase their chances of success.- Landing on a planet or station will just open up a transaction window but it doesnt have any animations, landing videos, or videos of your character interacting with the local merchants.- Turrent view seems awkward at times, its hard to shoot from the turrents while trying to drive your ship at the same time, whats the point of manning the guns if you have to pilot the ship at the same time? someone fire those lazy crew members of the player ships.- Weapons seem underpowered, in some fights you can be fighting enemy ships for 5-10 min before the enemy ship gets destroyed and you will have to wait for cooldown on lasers/plasma weapons to keep shooting.- Cargo space is very limited, you really have to decide what you wanna carry with you and how much money you want to make from loot. The game isnt very friendly if you want to play as a space trader making profit from trade.- There are no fleet options in the game yet to command your own fleet of ships.- Hacking enemy ship systems seems to not be in the game yet, at least there isnt any option to attempt to hack the enemy ships systems but there is gear that you can purchase to add % of chance to defend against hacking attempts on your ship.- Right now there isnt a story mode in the game yet, only a free roam mode.- The ""Free Roam"" mode has a game world that is divided into sectors each controlled by a mining station, space station, planet, or other big structure but none of those structures are capturable at the moment.Conclusion------------Its a very fun game to play with alot of potential for growth and improvement but right now the game isnt in a playable state that I would consider justified to buy it right now. The only reason that people should buy this game right now is if they want to support the developers or if they have hope for the future but with the way the video game industry is right now with games having a million DLC's to get a complete game having hope for the future with developers can often backfire.The developers are very active in the community page, answer questions, and comment on suggestions that the community makes to improve the game but the development team seems pretty small and progress is slow. It is my hope that the game does well and continues to improve but nobody knows how long it would take for the game to be at a stage where its considered complete and fun to play."
