76561197988914027,Not Recommended,236150,12297222,"Posted: 29 September, 2014",all,DarthDiddler,MEH!!!
,Not Recommended,236150,14052224,"Posted: 18 January, 2015",all,markais,"Great potential, but rather incomplete.This game should not be released as a completed game yet. There are many aspects of the game that are not implemented. Enemies cannot board your ship, though you can purchase upgrades to defend against this. Fighters, bombers and inteceptors all act the same, and there are no enemy fighters. Some structures have hit points, but you can't actually do anything to them. Graphics occasionally glitch or break. Ship class balance doesn't exist. Mission-critical enemies can't be targeted with auto-fire and fighters won't attack. Raising and lowering reputation with various factions doesn't seem to have much impact on the game. The list goes on.That said, it's still quite fun for a while. Despite occasional (very rare) glitches, the graphics are beautiful. The soundtrack is relaxing, if a bit unvaried. Customizing a ship for long, mid or short range combat can be rather fun. The controls take a bit of getting used to, but work smoothly once you get the hang of them. The ability to capture enemy ships with the choice of keeping or selling them is always a plus in my book.As much as I wanted to love this game, though, it fell short. The story had some interesting points, but was short and overall dull. Side missions were worthless and repetitive, with very low rewards and only a handful of variants. The bad grammar in the text and horrible fake accents in the voice acting detracted from the otherwise just passable story. There's really no incentive to explore all that much; I did simply because I always do in games, but found it didn't provide anything of worth to do so.If the developers ever finish the game, it could be decent, perhaps even great. In its current state, it will get hopes up and then let you down with the disapointment of spending money and time on something that needs quite a bit more time in development. Here's to hoping I can switch to recommending this game in the future."
