76561198121986034,Not Recommended,236150,22902298,"Posted: 10 May, 2016",all,zacharyhess,"This game has several issues, but a few good points, which I will list.Storyline: The campaign is your standard 'fight the Empire' campaign. It's not very interesting and honestly, is not enough to keep you locked into the game.Missions: Escort, kill, transport, scan. That's it. There isn't much to do and not much fun in doing it unless you really enjoy grinding the♥♥♥♥♥♥out of ships.Speaking of ships: They are expensive, as are the systems that use them. So get used to grinding for scrap material to sell for every single credit you can because my god is everything so expensive. You will be a higher grade officer on a ship that is well below your experience level. I guarantee it.Combat: You can take control of the canons yourself. Don't know why you would though. Camera controls in that mode make it useless and the autoaim is about 10x better than you will ever be at shooting other ships.Abilities: Marginally useful depending on the situation but unless you have the repair ability you aren't playing the right class.Now onto the positive stuff. Mods! Lots of really good mods to alter combat, add ships, and improve the cosmetics and trading. It really does make it a lot more fun to play when your ship isn't moving like and old woman up a hill all the time. Plus it makes it easier to get good weapon systems. The problem is, modding the game makes it very unstable. You will crash more than a Bethesda game.TLDR: If you are looking for a discount Elite Dangerous or Star Citizen, keep looking. This is not the game you want."
